<div id="review_906418301" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/906418301" />
    <a title="Ahmed Chowdhry" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/15198604-ahmed-chowdhry"><img alt="Ahmed Chowdhry" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1439475487p2/15198604.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/906418301?book_show_action=true">Apr 07, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ahmed Chowdhry" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ahmed Chowdhry" href="/user/show/15198604-ahmed-chowdhry">Ahmed Chowdhry</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer906418301" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14050320637331850628">This compulsively readable book put it all together in one seamless narrative, and replaced my slides with a breathtaking movie that has it all: epic battles, dynastic soap opera, noble patriotism, eyecatching eccentricity, treacherously shifting alliances, scheming and backstabbing and dazzling hypocrisy, with the survival of a great democracy always at stake and always at risk.<br/><br/>The cast of characters over here is the stuff of legends: Pompey the Great, the temporizing orator/politician Cicero, </span>
  <span id="freeText14050320637331850628" style="display:none">This compulsively readable book put it all together in one seamless narrative, and replaced my slides with a breathtaking movie that has it all: epic battles, dynastic soap opera, noble patriotism, eyecatching eccentricity, treacherously shifting alliances, scheming and backstabbing and dazzling hypocrisy, with the survival of a great democracy always at stake and always at risk.<br /><br />The cast of characters over here is the stuff of legends: Pompey the Great, the temporizing orator/politician Cicero, the slippery Mark Antony, Julius Caesar, Brutus, Mark Anthony, Spartacus, Cato, the exotic Cleopatra and the man who buried the Roman Republic and was the first emperor of the Roman Empire, Octavian (Augustus). <br /><br />The end of the Roman Republic, more so than the much later fall of the Roman Empire, is a tale worth pondering. Tom Holland has made this experience exceedingly enjoyable, not to mention educational.<br /><br />Highest recommendation.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="14050320637331850628" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


